articles.title: MTP Daily 1/10/20
articles.description: MTP Daily is a public affairs program hosted by Chuck Todd that follows the Trump administration and features the top news-makers of the day as they analyze and break down the issues.

articles.author: MSNBC.com
articles.title: Cory Booker ‘feels some kind of way’ about billionaires buying onto debate stage
articles.description: Cory Booker talks about the frustration he and his campaign feel about the wild scale of campaign ad spending.

articles.author: MSNBC.com
articles.title: Will some GOP senators vote to hear impeachment witnesses? 'I've had hope before that has been dashed,' says Booker
articles.description: Cory Booker discusses how Sen. Collins voting for Justice Kavanaugh exemplifies the cynicism he has towards Republicans breaking from their party.

articles.author: MSNBC.com
articles.title: Facebook's new decision to allow lies in political ads will benefit Trump
articles.description: Facebook announced this week that it would not take down ads with lies put up by politicians. Ben Collins weighs in on why this could put a thumb on the scale for Donald Trump.

articles.author: MSNBC.com
articles.title: Trump in 2011: A president could start a war with Iran for political survival
articles.description: In 2011, Donald Trump said that one way an American president could turn things around politically would be with a war with Iran.

articles.author: MPX
articles.title: Bernie Sanders leads in latest Iowa poll, weeks before caucuses
articles.description: A new Des Moines Register/CNN Poll has Senator Bernie Sanders leading the pack with 20%. He is trailed by Senator Elizabeth Warren with 17%.

articles.author: MSNBC.com
articles.title: Trump threatening to block Bolton testimony in impeachment trial
articles.description: Democrats are eager to hear from Former National Security Advisor John Bolton, who has expressed his willingness to testify under subpoena. However, in a Fox News interview, President Trump signaled that he'll try to prevent that from happening.

articles.title: AP: White House considering dramatic expansion of travel ban
articles.description: The Associated Press reports that the White House is mulling an expansion of the travel ban, “amid a renewed election- year focus on immigration by President Donald Trump.” Jonathan Lemire breaks down his latest.
